records.addlTxt:
DOC contacted the Court regarding status of PSI.
Due to COVID-19 quarantine issues, the PSI might not be completed in time for the Sentencing hearing scheduled for November 10, 2022. . 
Clerk provided information to the parties and proposed a back-up sentencing date.
Corrected Plea questionnaire, waiver of rights; filed and received.

Defendant Ethan Isiah Tyler in court, in custody.  Attorney Annamarie Amy Wineke in court for Ethan Isiah Tyler.  Attorney Jacob Daniel Corr in court for State of Wisconsin. 

Case in Court for Plea hearing. Discussion placed on the record. Parties have reached a resolution in this matter. State complied with Victim Notification. Plea hearing proceeded. Negotiations placed on the record, and confirmed by Defense and Defendant. 

STATE ORALLY AMENDED COUNT 1 and COUNT 2: TO REMOVE PENALTY ENHANCER: USE OF A DANGEROUS WEAPON, Sec. 939.63(1)(b).

AS TO AMENDED COUNT 1 AMENDED COUNT 2: 
Defendant changed his plea to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to the plea, and advised of Constitutional Rights and maximum penalties. Defendant advised that if he is not a US citizen, deportation is possible. Court found Defendant knowingly, voluntarily, and intelligently waived all his rights. Parties stipulated to the Criminal Complaint as a factual basis for the plea. Court found Defendant GUILTY as charged in the Information, and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction. 

Court advised Defendant that he is prohibited from firearm possession, ammunition, or body armor. 
Court advised Defendant that his voting rights are suspended, and he may not vote until his civil rights are restored.

Court ordered case adjourned for Sentencing hearing, Branch 46. Hearing will be held in Room 113 of the Safety Building. 

FILED: Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum, and Elements of the Offense/Jury Instructions.
Plea Questionnaire/ Waiver of Rights; received and filed.

Defendant Ethan Isiah Tyler in court with attorney Annamarie Amy Wineke.  Defendant Ethan Isiah Tyler in custody.  Jacob Daniel Corr appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

**PARTIES APPEARED VIA ZOOM VIDEO CONFERENCE.**
Case in Court for Plea hearing. Discussion placed on the record. Defense requested an adjournment, to allow time to continue discussions with Defendant. State did not object. Case adjourned for  Plea hearing. Case remains calendared in Branch 46. Plea hearing scheduled September 15, 2022 at 10:00 am. Hearing will held in room 113 of the Safety Building.

Defendant Ethan Isiah Tyler in Court with Attorney Annamarie Amy Wineke.  Defendant Ethan Isiah Tyler in custody.  Jacob Daniel Corr appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  

**PARTIES APPEARED VIA ZOOM VIDEO CONFERENCE.**
Case in Court for Scheduling Conference. Discussion placed on the record. Defense received discovery material and an offer from the State. Defense requested a plea date. State to comply with Victim Notification. Court ordered case adjourned for Plea hearing. Case remains calendared in Branch 46. Plea hearing scheduled for July 26, 2022 at 09:00 am. Hearing will be held IN-PERSON in Room 113 of the Safety Building.

Defendant Ethan Isiah Tyler in court, appear by video with attorney Annamarie Amy Wineke, appear by video.  Defendant Ethan Isiah Tyler in custody.  Adam Joseph Best appeared by video for the State of Wisconsin.  
Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Sworn for the State: Detective E. Rubio.   State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Original information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and plead not guilty.  Case is adjourned to Branch 46.  Scheduling conference scheduled for June 23, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Ethan Isiah Tyler in court with attorney Annamarie Amy Wineke.  Defendant Ethan Isiah Tyler in custody.  Jacob Daniel Corr appeared for the State of Wisconsin. 
**JUDGE FEISS AND ALL PARTIES APPEARED VIA ZOOM VIDEO CONFERENCE.**

Case calendared for an Order to Show Cause hearing. The State Public Defender's Office has appointed Attorney Wineke. Case is adjourned for preliminary hearing.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for June 10, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Ethan Isiah Tyler not in court, defendant in custody.  Navjot Singh Hira appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Case in court for preliminary hearing. Defendant not produced.  SPD has not appointed counsel at this time. State requests an Order to Show cause hearing. Court ordered case adjourned for CAUSE to Br. 46.  Order to show cause hearing scheduled for June 3, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 5.  No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Defendant Ethan Isiah Tyler in court with attorney Corey R. Flynn.  Defendant Ethan Isiah Tyler in custody.  Brittany Skye Kachingwe appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Ethan Isiah Tyler appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Feiss, Branch 46. Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold the defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL.  Commissioner advised DNA sample has NOT been obtained from the Defendant.  Court ordered the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department to obtain DNA sample from the Defendant.  Court advised Defendant he may qualify to have the DNA sample data expunged if he meets the conditions under Wisconsin Statutes Section 165.77(4).  
This hearing will be streamed live on Dacast:  https://iframe.dacast.com/live/4dafbf46-ed15-c11c-fa22-a58262833632/99073afd-37c2-acfa-830d-b1ddcaebf0ea  Preliminary hearing scheduled for May 26, 2022 at 08:30 am.
